{"TopicId":59587,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"How much a Kerbal weight?","CreatedByName":"FellipeC","CreatedById":77983,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-01-11T01:03:00Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"FellipeC","CreatedById":77983,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-01-11T01:03:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI just wonder if the same capsule with 1 or 3 kerbals weights different. If does, how much does a Kerbal weight?\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"LostElement","CreatedById":78368,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-01-11T01:07:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EWell they do weigh something. I had a very small rocket. It was about 1 or 2 tons. I placed and External Command seat on it and place a kerbal asymmetrically The rocket flipped out of control with out SAS, I tried with out the kerbal and it flew perfectly. I am curious to know this myself.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"lajoswinkler","CreatedById":79159,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-01-11T01:19:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E90 kg if I recall correctly, but their mass vanishes when they enter a pod.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FellipeC","CreatedById":77983,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-01-11T01:51:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022lajoswinkler\u0022 data-cite=\u0022lajoswinkler\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E90 kg if I recall correctly, but their mass vanishes when they enter a pod.\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESo they only weight when on a external command seat?\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"stupid_chris","CreatedById":62017,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-01-11T02:08:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022FellipeC\u0022 data-cite=\u0022FellipeC\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003ESo they only weight when on a external command seat?\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EExactly. They only have weight in EVA.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"lajoswinkler","CreatedById":79159,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-01-11T02:10:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022FellipeC\u0022 data-cite=\u0022FellipeC\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003ESo they only weight when on a external command seat?\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EYes, but only if in they\u0027re not moving in a gravitational field. Otherwise, they\u0027re weightless.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThey have mass, though. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kiwiak","CreatedById":82796,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-01-11T03:12:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022lajoswinkler\u0022 data-cite=\u0022lajoswinkler\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E90 kg if I recall correctly, but their mass vanishes when they enter a pod.\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis needs to be be fixed.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"UmbralRaptor","CreatedById":2767,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-01-11T05:22:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EExactly .09375 tonnes (regardless of fuel state) when outside a pod, 0 when inside.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Castille7","CreatedById":101668,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-25T11:49:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u0022891790\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002259587\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221389409975\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002282796\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kiwiak\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 1/10/2014 at 9:12 PM, kiwiak said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis needs to be be fixed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/82796-kiwiak/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002282796\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/82796-kiwiak/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@kiwiak\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0This seems to be fixed, I just experienced this during flight test with my \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/60345-work-in-progress-wip-design-thread/\u0026amp;do=findComment\u0026amp;comment=2820270\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EWSH-500\u003C/a\u003E craft. I have the craft designed with low power Wheesley Engines to give it a realistic effect.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-10-25T11:49:52Z\u0022 title=\u002210/25/2016 11:49  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 25, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Castille7\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Peder","CreatedById":57860,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-25T11:54:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWeight depend upon how many snacks they eat before takeoff, so it can variate ;-)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}